CHANGES

This file describe remarkable change in user's view.

From 2.105:
  - fix around text clipping (surface string)
  - rearrange port/board string position
  - rearrange around arrow head; clip ends when "NORMAL"-head
  - fix around DIRECT and DIRECT1 style in vertical SCATTER/GATHER
  - introduce HWSLIT and fix slits
  - introduce slitpos and slitthick for slits

From 2.104:
  - rearrange color map
      * it accepts named color.  naming by NAMEDCOLOR
      * it accepts hex style color speicication (c.f. 333H, fedh)

From 2.103:
  - expand color map
  - employ RMIKUZUSI (45 degree rotated MIKUZUSI) hatch pattern

From 2.102:
  - employ note NWI, NWO, NNWO, WNWO and simular
  - employ MIKUZUSI hatch pattern

From 2.101
  - fix chop in chop_seg

From 2.100
  - support vertical SCATTER/GATHER
  - improve default size of PLINE and SEP
  - fix arround expand_sep

From 2.099
  - new object PIE with PIESTART and PIEEND

From 2.098
  - care simple CURVE (no FROM and TO)
  - arrange fontset configuration
        kanji.all=Osaka;kanji.all.encode=CP932

From 2.097
  - employ option -e for external ouput charset
    however, it is change to attribute of font, maybe
  - care external input/output and internal charset
  - re-support 'chop' in LINE and related
  - re-implementation CRANK/ELBOW
  - employ CRANK/ELBOW

From 2.096
  - support 'rad' in DRUM and PIPE
        can change the size of ellipse in tall height drum 
        and long length pipe.

From 2.060
  - support UTF-8 source, but care only Japanese
        using cheap trick, this version parses UTF-8 source.
        then, this version requires iconv (-liconv).
        of course it requires some Japanese font.
        IPAMincho is setted as default.

From 2.052
  - arrange port/board string
        fit them according to curves and lines in
        CURVE family and simple lines in LINE family.

From 2.051
  - change width of THRU
        from 1.0u to 1.5u to keep margin for arrows.

From 2.050
  - chang width of SACTTER/GATHER
        from 1.0u to 1.5u to keep margin for arrows.

From 2.045
  - shape of CARD
        currently shapes is left upper corner cut-offed.
  - change name CLINE to ULINE
        ULINE is user defined line sequence.
